FBIS3-18635 "drweu044_j_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-044 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Mar 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Fabbri Comments on Sending Troops to Bosnia LD0503110194 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 0800 GMT 5 Mar 94 LD0503110194 Rome RAI Due Television Network Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Text] Italian soldiers could be sent to Bosnia to reinforce the UN peacekeeping contingent. France and Great Britain have requested this from UN Secretary General Butrus-Ghali. Foreign Minister Beniamino Andreatta said that he has not yet received any official request but that he would not set any conditions. Although Defense Minister Fabio Fabbri has not denied the possibility, he pointed out that the government would have to make a collective decision.
